  <name>Redragon HS Companion</name>
  <summary>Volume control for Redragon wireless headsets</summary>

  <description>
    <p>
      Redragon HS Companion is a complete solution for controlling the volume of Redragon wireless headsets
      (H878, H848, H510, etc.) on Linux.
    </p>
    <p>Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Fast command-line control with ~20ms response time</li>
      <li>Automatic PCM channel synchronization daemon</li>
      <li>Graphical interface for GNOME Shell, Cinnamon, and KDE Plasma</li>
      <li>Auto-detection of connected headsets</li>
      <li>Support for both analog and digital audio outputs</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      The application solves the issue where PipeWire only controls one of the headset's PCM channels,
      leaving the other out of sync, which causes volume problems and unbalanced audio.
    </p>
  </description>

